headlines.description: Kyle Washington had 17 points with eight rebounds and No. 6 Cincinnati remained undefeated in American Athletic Conference play, stretching its overall winning streak to 16 games with a 76-51 victory over short-handed SMU on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 6 Cincinnati routs short-handed SMU for 16th win in row

video.headline: Cincinnati gets road win over SMU

headlines.description: Grayson Allen scored 23 points and No. 9 Duke beat Georgia Tech 80-69 on Sunday night to end a two-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 9 Duke beats Georgia Tech to end 2-game losing streak

video.headline: Duke rolls to victory over Georgia Tech

headlines.description: Moe Wagner scored 20 points, went 8 of 14 from the field and added 11 rebounds, and No. 20 Michigan rode a hot-shooting first half for an 83-72 win over Wisconsin on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hot-shooting 1st half helps No. 20 Michigan beat Wisconsin

video.headline: Michigan holds off Wisconsin for 20th win

headlines.description: Matt Klinewski scored 25 points and Lafayette defeated Loyola-Maryland 84-67 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klinewski scores 25 points in Lafayette's 84-67 victory

headlines.description: Anas Mahmoud scored 14 points to lead Louisville to a 94-60 win over Pittsburgh on Sunday.
Tyus Battle scored 34 points, Oshae Brissett added 15 points and 10 rebounds, and Syracuse held off Wake Forest 78-70 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Battle scores 34, Syracuse holds off Wake Forest 78-70

headlines.description: Jairus Lyles scored 18 points, Jourdan Grant added 14 and UMBC won at New Hampshire for the first time in six years, 68-59, on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lyles leads UMBC past UNH 68-59 despite Leissner's record

headlines.description: Brandon Armstrong scored a career-high 24 points on 9-of-11 shooting and Tyler Hagedorn added 19 and South Dakota beat NAIA Peru State of Nebraska, 98-55 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: S. Dakota takes down NAIA-member Peru St. 98-55

headlines.description: Joe Cremo scored 21 points, Travis Charles had 14 and nine rebounds and Albany beat Harford 69-63 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Albany keeps Hartford at bay with 69-63 win behind Cremo

headlines.description: Mike Holloway Jr. scored 23 points and Darnell Edge added 22, including all eight of his free throws down the stretch, and Fairleigh Dickinson upset Northeast Conference leader Wagner 76-69 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fairleigh Dickinson upsets NEC leader Wagner 76-69

headlines.description: Akwasi Yeboah scored with 44 seconds left for the lead and Tyrell Sturdivant added three free throws in Stony Brook's 64-61 victory over Maine on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stony Brook continues dominance of Maine with 64-61 win

headlines.description: Trae Bell-Haynes tied a career-high with 27 points to surpass 1,500 career points and Vermont won its 14th straight with an 81-69 victory over UMass Lowell on Sunday to clinch a home playoff game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vermont wins 14th straight, 81-69 over UMass Lowell

headlines.description: B.J. Taylor scored 22 points and made a key shot and two free throws with 16 seconds to help Central Florida beat Memphis 68-64 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: UCF ends two-game skid beating Memphis 68-64

headlines.description: Lucas Siewert scored a career-high 17 points, including a pair of 3-pointers down the stretch, and the Colorado Buffaloes beat the Stanford Cardinal 64-56 Sunday for their third win in a row.
headlines.shortLinkText: Buffs win third straight as Colorado downs Stanford 64-56

headlines.description: Kavion Pippen scored 21 points with eight rebounds and four blocks and Southern Illinois defeated Bradley 74-57 on Sunday to take over sole possession of second place in the Missouri Valley Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Southern Illinois alone in 2nd in MVC after win over Bradley

headlines.description: Bakari Evelyn scored 22 points with four 3-pointers, Max Joseph had 10 of his 12 points in the second half and Valparaiso beat short-handed Illinois State 74-58 on Sunday.

Devin Davis scored 16 points, Armoni Brooks had a double-double and Houston throttled Tulane 73-42 on Sunday to stay in a tie for second place in the American Athletic Conference standings with Wichita State.
Shep Garner scored 16 points and Tony Carr had 15 points to lead Penn State to a 74-52 victory over Illinois on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garner, Carr help Penn State beat Illinois 74-52

headlines.description: Payton Pritchard had 19 points and 10 assists, and Troy Brown Jr. also had a double-double to lead Oregon past Washington State 84-57 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pritchard, Brown lead Oregon to 84-57 win over Washington St

nowFeed.headline: Oklahoma's Trae Young, on his recent offensive struggles: "Im getting guarded like nobody else in the country is being guarded, scouted on like no one else in the country. Its a mystery coming out each and every game to try and figure out how a team is going to guard me and how Im going to dictate how my team wins.  Its a lot tougher for me to score now than it was in the beginning. ... Its a process. Right now, its tough."
